<br>
Then how about: &quot;PLANETARY EVOLUTION (other then Earth's)&quot;<br>
<br>
Unlike frozen Mars, there's a darn good chance that something (perhaps lizard like) could respond.<br>
<br>
Take a look at what my research has turned up: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://guthvenus.tripod.com">guthvenus.tripod.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> and as backup URL <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://geocities.com/bradguth">geocities.com/bradguth</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I don't want to become a pest, but folks, we have an opportunity here to do something that's not political, not NSA/DoD and thereby not likely to generate another 9/11. The cost of this communications effort is not 1% of what sending another Magellan satellite back to Venus is worth. There is nothing to lose, except self respect if you've been an avid pro-NASA supporter (so what's the big deal?). Self respect is cheap as compared to the alternatives, which is stupidity and subsequent arrogance. Look at where that's got us.<br>
<br>
